casebody.data:
The State, ex rel. Aqeel, Appellant, v. Bettman, Judge, Appellee.

[Cite as State, ex rel. Aqeel, v. Bettman (1989), 43 Ohio St. 3d 156.]

(No. 88-822 Submitted April 4 , 1989 Decided June 14, 1989.) Abid H. Aqeel, pro se. Arthur M. Ney, Jr., prosecuting attorney, and William E. Breyer, for appellee.

The judgment of the court of appeals sustaining the respondent’s motion to dismiss the petition for a writ of mandamus on the basis that a previous ruling of that court is res judicata is affirmed.

Moyer, C.J., Sweeney, Holmes, Douglas, Wright, H. Brown and Resnick, JJ., concur.
